14/07/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- A passenger train collided with freight cars early Monday (July 14th), injuring the train engineer and 15 passengers, media reported. 
It happened in the district of Phtiotida, central Greece. 
The passenger train, bound from Thessaloniki to Athens, ran into cars detached from a freight train. 
Several hundred passengers had to be evacuated and bused to Athens. 
Authorities closed the Thessaloniki-Athens rail line. 
Police detained two freight train engineers in connection with the accident. 
(SKAI, ANA-MPA, Naftemporiki, In.news - 14/07/08)
